# scrub-personal-tokens.txt.example
#
# Copy to ~/.scrub-personal-tokens.txt and edit with YOUR personal tokens.
# One regex pattern per line. # comments allowed.
# Empty lines ignored.
#
# The pre-commit-template.sh hook will refuse any public-repo commit
# where the staged diff contains lines matching ANY of these patterns.

# Word-boundary tokens (use \b...\b). For names, companies, cities, products
# whose substrings might legitimately appear inside other words. Example:
# \b(Acme|YourFullName|YourCofounder|YourCity)\b

# Path-style tokens (no word-boundary needed). For private repo names,
# personal vault paths, internal product names. Example:
# (your-private-repo|/path/to/your/personal/vault)

# Specific phrases (no word-boundary). For book titles, newsletter names,
# program names, anything with internal spaces. Example:
# (Your Book Series|Your Newsletter Name|Your Cohort Program)

# Email-shaped tokens. Example:
# (you@example\.com|admin@yourdomain\.com)
